<p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1rem; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;; font-size: 15px; letter-spacing: normal;">Operations Bridge Manager (OBM) and Operations Agent, provide an inbuilt, self-signed certificate based, secure communication framework. This secure communication framework provides strong security, adhering to industry standards. However, for certain organizations, it is mandatory to use a specific recommended Certificate Authority (CA). For such occasions, it is possible to use a third party CA, in place of the inbuilt certificate management framework. This topic provides all the necessary steps to use a third party CA for a secure communication environment in a distributed OBM, Operations Agent deployment scenario.</p><p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1rem; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;; font-size: 15px; letter-spacing: normal;">This topic assumes fresh installation of OBM and Operations Agent systems as the starting point, which are not configured yet. The steps provided include, the steps to create certificates on the OBM Server (additional steps required for a distributed OBM setup), and steps to create certificates on the Operations Agent system. The subsequent topics provide details of all the steps to should be followed.</p><div name="CreatingcertificatesonstandaloneOBMserver[edit|editsource]" data-unique="CreatingcertificatesonstandaloneOBMserver[edit|editsource]" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;; font-size: 15px;"></div><h2 style="box-sizing: border-box; background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; font-weight: 500; margin: 25px 0px 6px; overflow: hidden; padding-top: 0em; padding-bottom: 0.17em; border-bottom: none; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;; line-height: 1.2; letter-spacing: normal; text-transform: none; color: rgb(0, 115, 231) !important; font-size: 24px !important;"><span class="mw-headline" id="Creating_certificates_on_standalone_OBM_server" style="box-sizing: border-box;">Creating certificates on standalone OBM server</span></h2><p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1rem; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;; font-size: 15px; letter-spacing: normal;">This task explains the steps to install certificates from a third party CA on a standalone OBM system.</p><ol style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0.3em 0px 0px 3.2em; padding: 0px; list-style-image: none; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;; font-size: 15px;"><li style="box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 0.65em; list-style-type: decimal; margin-left: 8px; margin-top: 0.65em;">Install OBM using the installation wizard, but do not execute the configuration step. At this point all the core ids (server OVRG groups and the nodes), will be same as shown in the following image.<br style="box-sizing: border-box;"><a href="https://docs.microfocus.com/itomw/File:OBM_2018.05_CAImg1.PNG" class="image" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(58, 131, 230); background: none transparent;"><img alt="OBM 2018.05 CAImg1.PNG" src="https://docs.microfocus.com/mediawiki/images/5/55/OBM_2018.05_CAImg1.PNG" width="618" height="418" data-file-width="618" data-file-height="418" style="box-sizing: border-box; border: none; vertical-align: middle; max-width: 100%;"></a><br style="box-sizing: border-box;">This feature is available from OBM 2018.05 release.</li><li style="box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 0.65em; list-style-type: decimal; margin-left: 8px; margin-top: 0.65em;">Remove all the certificates that are present.<ul style="box-sizing: border-box; list-style-type: disc; margin: 0.3em 0px 0px 1.6em; padding: 0px;"><li style="box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 0.65em; list-style-type: disc; margin-left: 6px; margin-top: 0.65em;">You can do this by running the&nbsp;<code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, &quot;Liberation Mono&quot;, &quot;Courier New&quot;, monospace; color: rgb(232, 62, 140); background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); border-width: 1px; border-style: solid; border-color: rgb(234, 236, 240); border-radius: 2px; font-size: 13.125px; word-break: break-word; padding: 2px 5px !important;">ovcert –remove &lt;certificate id&gt;</code>&nbsp;command.</li><li style="box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 0.65em; list-style-type: disc; margin-left: 6px; margin-top: 0.65em;">You should run the command for both the node and trusted certificate.</li><li style="box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 0.65em; list-style-type: disc; margin-left: 6px; margin-top: 0.65em;">To remove the certificates in the resource group&nbsp;<span style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: bolder;">OVRG: Server</span>, run the following command:<br style="box-sizing: border-box;"><code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, &quot;Liberation Mono&quot;, &quot;Courier New&quot;, monospace; color: rgb(232, 62, 140); background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); border-width: 1px; border-style: solid; border-color: rgb(234, 236, 240); border-radius: 2px; font-size: 13.125px; word-break: break-word; padding: 2px 5px !important;">ovcert –remove &lt;certificate id&gt; -ovrg server</code><br style="box-sizing: border-box;">For example, see the following image:<br style="box-sizing: border-box;"><a href="https://docs.microfocus.com/itomw/File:OBM_2018.05_CAImg2.PNG" class="image" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(58, 131, 230); background: none transparent;"><img alt="OBM 2018.05 CAImg2.PNG" src="https://docs.microfocus.com/mediawiki/images/e/ed/OBM_2018.05_CAImg2.PNG" width="957" height="178" data-file-width="957" data-file-height="178" style="box-sizing: border-box; border: none; vertical-align: middle; max-width: 100%;"></a></li></ul></li><li style="box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 0.65em; list-style-type: decimal; margin-left: 8px; margin-top: 0.65em;">The Keystore Content should be empty after removing the certificates. This can be verified using the&nbsp;<code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, &quot;Liberation Mono&quot;, &quot;Courier New&quot;, monospace; color: rgb(232, 62, 140); background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); border-width: 1px; border-style: solid; border-color: rgb(234, 236, 240); border-radius: 2px; font-size: 13.125px; word-break: break-word; padding: 2px 5px !important;">ovcert –list</code>&nbsp;command. The output of&nbsp;<code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, &quot;Liberation Mono&quot;, &quot;Courier New&quot;, monospace; color: rgb(232, 62, 140); background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); border-width: 1px; border-style: solid; border-color: rgb(234, 236, 240); border-radius: 2px; font-size: 13.125px; word-break: break-word; padding: 2px 5px !important;">ovcert –list</code>&nbsp;command should appear as shown in the following image:<br style="box-sizing: border-box;"><a href="https://docs.microfocus.com/itomw/File:OBM_2018.05_CAImg3.PNG" class="image" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(58, 131, 230); background: none transparent;"><img alt="OBM 2018.05 CAImg3.PNG" src="https://docs.microfocus.com/mediawiki/images/6/6e/OBM_2018.05_CAImg3.PNG" width="690" height="329" data-file-width="690" data-file-height="329" style="box-sizing: border-box; border: none; vertical-align: middle; max-width: 100%;"></a></li><li style="box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 0.65em; list-style-type: decimal; margin-left: 8px; margin-top: 0.65em;">It is important that the server resource group&nbsp;<span style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: bolder;">OVRG</span>&nbsp;has a different core identifier. A different core identifier can be created using the&nbsp;<code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, &quot;Liberation Mono&quot;, &quot;Courier New&quot;, monospace; color: rgb(232, 62, 140); background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); border-width: 1px; border-style: solid; border-color: rgb(234, 236, 240); border-radius: 2px; font-size: 13.125px; word-break: break-word; padding: 2px 5px !important;">ovcoreid –create –force –ovrg server</code>&nbsp;command, as shown in the following image:<br style="box-sizing: border-box;"><a href="https://docs.microfocus.com/itomw/File:OBM_2018.05_CAImg4.PNG" class="image" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(58, 131, 230); background: none transparent;"><img alt="OBM 2018.05 CAImg4.PNG" src="https://docs.microfocus.com/mediawiki/images/e/e6/OBM_2018.05_CAImg4.PNG" width="826" height="71" data-file-width="826" data-file-height="71" style="box-sizing: border-box; border: none; vertical-align: middle; max-width: 100%;"></a></li><li style="box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 0.65em; list-style-type: decimal; margin-left: 8px; margin-top: 0.65em;">You can use the preferred third party CA to issue two certificates as follows:<ul style="box-sizing: border-box; list-style-type: disc; margin: 0.3em 0px 0px 1.6em; padding: 0px;"><li style="box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 0.65em; list-style-type: disc; margin-left: 6px; margin-top: 0.65em;">For the node with the CN from the output of&nbsp;<code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, &quot;Liberation Mono&quot;, &quot;Courier New&quot;, monospace; color: rgb(232, 62, 140); background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); border-width: 1px; border-style: solid; border-color: rgb(234, 236, 240); border-radius: 2px; font-size: 13.125px; word-break: break-word; padding: 2px 5px !important;">ovcoreid</code>&nbsp;command.</li><li style="box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 0.65em; list-style-type: disc; margin-left: 6px; margin-top: 0.65em;">For the server with the CN from the output of&nbsp;<code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, &quot;Liberation Mono&quot;, &quot;Courier New&quot;, monospace; color: rgb(232, 62, 140); background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); border-width: 1px; border-style: solid; border-color: rgb(234, 236, 240); border-radius: 2px; font-size: 13.125px; word-break: break-word; padding: 2px 5px !important;">ovcoreid -ovrg server</code>&nbsp;command.<br style="box-sizing: border-box;">These certificates must be in p12 format.<br style="box-sizing: border-box;">Create a copy of the trusted CA certificate in pem format. Copy the certificates to the OBM server.</li></ul></li><li style="box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 0.65em; list-style-type: decimal; margin-left: 8px; margin-top: 0.65em;">Import to the node and server certificates generated as follows:<ol style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0.3em 0px 0px 3.2em; padding: 0px; list-style-image: none;"><li style="box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 0.65em; list-style-type: lower-alpha; margin-left: 4px; margin-top: 0.65em;">Import the trusted certificate in to the server and server resource group, run the following commands:<ol style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0.3em 0px 0px 3.2em; padding: 0px; list-style-image: none;"><li style="box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 0.65em; list-style-type: lower-roman; margin-left: 8px; margin-top: 0.65em;"><code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, &quot;Liberation Mono&quot;, &quot;Courier New&quot;, monospace; color: rgb(232, 62, 140); background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); border-width: 1px; border-style: solid; border-color: rgb(234, 236, 240); border-radius: 2px; font-size: 13.125px; word-break: break-word; padding: 2px 5px !important;">ovcert –importtrusted –file &lt;certificate file&gt; -ovrg server</code></li><li style="box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 0.65em; list-style-type: lower-roman; margin-left: 8px; margin-top: 0.65em;"><code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, &quot;Liberation Mono&quot;, &quot;Courier New&quot;, monospace; color: rgb(232, 62, 140); background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); border-width: 1px; border-style: solid; border-color: rgb(234, 236, 240); border-radius: 2px; font-size: 13.125px; word-break: break-word; padding: 2px 5px !important;">ovcert –importtrusted –file &lt;certificate file&gt;</code><br style="box-sizing: border-box;">For example, see the following image:<br style="box-sizing: border-box;"><a href="https://docs.microfocus.com/itomw/File:OBM_2018.05_CAImg5.PNG" class="image" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(58, 131, 230); background: none transparent;"><img alt="OBM 2018.05 CAImg5.PNG" src="https://docs.microfocus.com/mediawiki/images/9/90/OBM_2018.05_CAImg5.PNG" width="819" height="133" data-file-width="819" data-file-height="133" style="box-sizing: border-box; border: none; vertical-align: middle; max-width: 100%;"></a></li></ol></li><li style="box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 0.65em; list-style-type: lower-alpha; margin-left: 4px; margin-top: 0.65em;">After importing the trusted certificate, import the server and node certificate. Run the following commands:<ol style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0.3em 0px 0px 3.2em; padding: 0px; list-style-image: none;"><li style="box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 0.65em; list-style-type: lower-roman; margin-left: 8px; margin-top: 0.65em;"><code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, &quot;Liberation Mono&quot;, &quot;Courier New&quot;, monospace; color: rgb(232, 62, 140); background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); border-width: 1px; border-style: solid; border-color: rgb(234, 236, 240); border-radius: 2px; font-size: 13.125px; word-break: break-word; padding: 2px 5px !important;">ovcert –importcert –file &lt;server certificate file&gt; -ovrg server</code></li><li style="box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 0.65em; list-style-type: lower-roman; margin-left: 8px; margin-top: 0.65em;"><code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, &quot;Liberation Mono&quot;, &quot;Courier New&quot;, monospace; color: rgb(232, 62, 140); background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); border-width: 1px; border-style: solid; border-color: rgb(234, 236, 240); border-radius: 2px; font-size: 13.125px; word-break: break-word; padding: 2px 5px !important;">ovcert –importcert –file &lt;node certificate file&gt;</code><br style="box-sizing: border-box;">For example, see the following image:<br style="box-sizing: border-box;"><a href="https://docs.microfocus.com/itomw/File:OBM_2018.05_CAImg6.PNG" class="image" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(58, 131, 230); background: none transparent;"><img alt="OBM 2018.05 CAImg6.PNG" src="https://docs.microfocus.com/mediawiki/images/d/d0/OBM_2018.05_CAImg6.PNG" width="813" height="193" data-file-width="813" data-file-height="193" style="box-sizing: border-box; border: none; vertical-align: middle; max-width: 100%;"></a></li></ol></li><li style="box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 0.65em; list-style-type: lower-alpha; margin-left: 4px; margin-top: 0.65em;">Execute the config server wizard and re-check the certificate status. After executing the configuration wizard, the certificate generated by the third party CA should be present and active as shown in the following image:<br style="box-sizing: border-box;"><a href="https://docs.microfocus.com/itomw/File:OBM_2018.05_CAImg7.PNG" class="image" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(58, 131, 230); background: none transparent;"><img alt="OBM 2018.05 CAImg7.PNG" src="https://docs.microfocus.com/mediawiki/images/7/78/OBM_2018.05_CAImg7.PNG" width="713" height="465" data-file-width="713" data-file-height="465" style="box-sizing: border-box; border: none; vertical-align: middle; max-width: 100%;"></a><br style="box-sizing: border-box;">Also check the issuer CN of the newly imported certificates. It should be of the third party CA as shown in the following image:<br style="box-sizing: border-box;"><a href="https://docs.microfocus.com/itomw/File:OBM_2018.05_CAImg8.PNG" class="image" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(58, 131, 230); background: none transparent;"><img alt="OBM 2018.05 CAImg8.PNG" src="https://docs.microfocus.com/mediawiki/images/6/6b/OBM_2018.05_CAImg8.PNG" width="979" height="393" data-file-width="979" data-file-height="393" style="box-sizing: border-box; border: none; vertical-align: middle; max-width: 100%;"></a></li></ol></li></ol><div name="CreatingcertificatesinadistributedOBMinstallation[edit|editsource]" data-unique="CreatingcertificatesinadistributedOBMinstallation[edit|editsource]" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;; font-size: 15px;"></div><h2 style="box-sizing: border-box; background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; font-weight: 500; margin: 25px 0px 6px; overflow: hidden; padding-top: 0em; padding-bottom: 0.17em; border-bottom: none; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;; line-height: 1.2; letter-spacing: normal; text-transform: none; color: rgb(0, 115, 231) !important; font-size: 24px !important;"><span class="mw-headline" id="Creating_certificates_in_a_distributed_OBM_installation" style="box-sizing: border-box;">Creating certificates in a distributed OBM installation</span></h2><p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1rem; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;; font-size: 15px; letter-spacing: normal;">A distributed OBM installation can include multiple Data Processing Systems (DPS) and Gateways. In this section, let us consider a setup with two DPS systems and two Gateway systems.</p><ol style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0.3em 0px 0px 3.2em; padding: 0px; list-style-image: none; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;; font-size: 15px;"><li style="box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 0.65em; list-style-type: decimal; margin-left: 8px; margin-top: 0.65em;">For the first DPS system, follow all the steps mentioned in&nbsp;<i style="box-sizing: border-box;">Creating certificates on standalone OBM server</i>&nbsp;section above.</li><li style="box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 0.65em; list-style-type: decimal; margin-left: 8px; margin-top: 0.65em;">Each node needs its own certificate based on its own unique ovcoreid. Issue a node certificate for the backup DPS with the CN from the output of the ovcoreid command. The certificate must be in p12 format. Copy the certificate to the backup DPS.</li><li style="box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 0.65em; list-style-type: decimal; margin-left: 8px; margin-top: 0.65em;">Copy both the trusted certificate file and server certificate file from the primary DPS (step 5 in&nbsp;<i style="box-sizing: border-box;">Creating certificates on standalone OBM server</i>) to the backup DPS. The system should have OBM installed, but not configured.</li><li style="box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 0.65em; list-style-type: decimal; margin-left: 8px; margin-top: 0.65em;">On the backup DPS system, import the trusted, server and node certificates to the default resource group and execute the configuration wizard. The steps are same as that in&nbsp;<i style="box-sizing: border-box;">Creating certificates on standalone OBM server</i>&nbsp;section above, steps 6 a and b.</li><li style="box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 0.65em; list-style-type: decimal; margin-left: 8px; margin-top: 0.65em;">On both the gateway systems, perform the following steps:<ol style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0.3em 0px 0px 3.2em; padding: 0px; list-style-image: none;"><li style="box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 0.65em; list-style-type: lower-alpha; margin-left: 4px; margin-top: 0.65em;">Issue a node certificate specifying the agent core id (ovcoreid) as the common name (CN).</li><li style="box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 0.65em; list-style-type: lower-alpha; margin-left: 4px; margin-top: 0.65em;">Copy the node certificate to the gateway system.</li><li style="box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 0.65em; list-style-type: lower-alpha; margin-left: 4px; margin-top: 0.65em;">Copy the trusted certificate file from the DPS.</li><li style="box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 0.65em; list-style-type: lower-alpha; margin-left: 4px; margin-top: 0.65em;">Run the following command to import the trusted certificate:<br style="box-sizing: border-box;"><code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, &quot;Liberation Mono&quot;, &quot;Courier New&quot;, monospace; color: rgb(232, 62, 140); background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); border-width: 1px; border-style: solid; border-color: rgb(234, 236, 240); border-radius: 2px; font-size: 13.125px; word-break: break-word; padding: 2px 5px !important;">ovcert -importtrusted -file &lt;certificate file&gt;</code></li><li style="box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 0.65em; list-style-type: lower-alpha; margin-left: 4px; margin-top: 0.65em;">Run the following command to import the node certificate:<br style="box-sizing: border-box;"><code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, &quot;Liberation Mono&quot;, &quot;Courier New&quot;, monospace; color: rgb(232, 62, 140); background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); border-width: 1px; border-style: solid; border-color: rgb(234, 236, 240); border-radius: 2px; font-size: 13.125px; word-break: break-word; padding: 2px 5px !important;">ovcert -importcert -file &lt;node certificate file&gt;</code></li><li style="box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 0.65em; list-style-type: lower-alpha; margin-left: 4px; margin-top: 0.65em;">Execute the configuration wizard. After running the config wizard, the&nbsp;<code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, &quot;Liberation Mono&quot;, &quot;Courier New&quot;, monospace; color: rgb(232, 62, 140); background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); border-width: 1px; border-style: solid; border-color: rgb(234, 236, 240); border-radius: 2px; font-size: 13.125px; word-break: break-word; padding: 2px 5px !important;">ovcert –list</code>&nbsp;output will list the certificate. For example, see the following image:<br style="box-sizing: border-box;"><a href="https://docs.microfocus.com/itomw/File:OBM_2018.05_CAimag12.PNG" class="image" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(58, 131, 230); background: none transparent;"><img alt="OBM 2018.05 CAimag12.PNG" src="https://docs.microfocus.com/mediawiki/images/6/6d/OBM_2018.05_CAimag12.PNG" width="683" height="243" data-file-width="683" data-file-height="243" style="box-sizing: border-box; border: none; vertical-align: middle; max-width: 100%;"></a></li></ol></li><li style="box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 0.65em; list-style-type: decimal; margin-left: 8px; margin-top: 0.65em;">Start the OBM server and check if all process are up on both GWs and DPS.</li></ol><div name="CreatingcertificatesontheOperationsAgentsystem[edit|editsource]" data-unique="CreatingcertificatesontheOperationsAgentsystem[edit|editsource]" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;; font-size: 15px;"></div><h2 style="box-sizing: border-box; background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; font-weight: 500; margin: 25px 0px 6px; overflow: hidden; padding-top: 0em; padding-bottom: 0.17em; border-bottom: none; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;; line-height: 1.2; letter-spacing: normal; text-transform: none; color: rgb(0, 115, 231) !important; font-size: 24px !important;"><span class="mw-headline" id="Creating_certificates_on_the_Operations_Agent_system" style="box-sizing: border-box;">Creating certificates on the Operations Agent system</span></h2><ol style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0.3em 0px 0px 3.2em; padding: 0px; list-style-image: none; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;; font-size: 15px;"><li style="box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 0.65em; list-style-type: decimal; margin-left: 8px; margin-top: 0.65em;">Create a profile file as follows:<br style="box-sizing: border-box;"><code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, &quot;Liberation Mono&quot;, &quot;Courier New&quot;, monospace; color: rgb(232, 62, 140); background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); border-width: 1px; border-style: solid; border-color: rgb(234, 236, 240); border-radius: 2px; font-size: 13.125px; word-break: break-word; padding: 2px 5px !important;">set sec.cm.client:CERTIFICATE_DEPLOYMENT_TYPE=MANUAL</code></li><li style="box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 0.65em; list-style-type: decimal; margin-left: 8px; margin-top: 0.65em;">Install the Operations Agent with the command:<ul style="box-sizing: border-box; list-style-type: disc; margin: 0.3em 0px 0px 1.6em; padding: 0px;"><li style="box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 0.65em; list-style-type: disc; margin-left: 6px; margin-top: 0.65em;">On UNIX/Linux:&nbsp;<code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, &quot;Liberation Mono&quot;, &quot;Courier New&quot;, monospace; color: rgb(232, 62, 140); background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); border-width: 1px; border-style: solid; border-color: rgb(234, 236, 240); border-radius: 2px; font-size: 13.125px; word-break: break-word; padding: 2px 5px !important;">./oainstall.sh -i -a -agent_profile &lt;path&gt;/&lt;profile_file&gt; -s &lt;management_server&gt;</code></li><li style="box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 0.65em; list-style-type: disc; margin-left: 6px; margin-top: 0.65em;">On Windows:&nbsp;<code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, &quot;Liberation Mono&quot;, &quot;Courier New&quot;, monospace; color: rgb(232, 62, 140); background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); border-width: 1px; border-style: solid; border-color: rgb(234, 236, 240); border-radius: 2px; font-size: 13.125px; word-break: break-word; padding: 2px 5px !important;">cscript oainstall.vbs -i -a -agent_profile &lt;path&gt;\&lt;profile_file&gt; -s &lt;management_server&gt;</code><br style="box-sizing: border-box;">In this instance,&nbsp;<code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, &quot;Liberation Mono&quot;, &quot;Courier New&quot;, monospace; color: rgb(232, 62, 140); background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); border-width: 1px; border-style: solid; border-color: rgb(234, 236, 240); border-radius: 2px; font-size: 13.125px; word-break: break-word; padding: 2px 5px !important;">&lt;path&gt;</code>&nbsp;is the path to the profile file.<br style="box-sizing: border-box;"><code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, &quot;Liberation Mono&quot;, &quot;Courier New&quot;, monospace; color: rgb(232, 62, 140); background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); border-width: 1px; border-style: solid; border-color: rgb(234, 236, 240); border-radius: 2px; font-size: 13.125px; word-break: break-word; padding: 2px 5px !important;">&lt;profile_file&gt;</code>&nbsp;is the name of the profile file.<br style="box-sizing: border-box;"><code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, &quot;Liberation Mono&quot;, &quot;Courier New&quot;, monospace; color: rgb(232, 62, 140); background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); border-width: 1px; border-style: solid; border-color: rgb(234, 236, 240); border-radius: 2px; font-size: 13.125px; word-break: break-word; padding: 2px 5px !important;">&lt;management_server&gt;</code>&nbsp;is the FQDN of the management server.<br style="box-sizing: border-box;">For more information to install Operations Agent, see&nbsp;<i style="box-sizing: border-box;">Operations Agent</i>&nbsp;documentation.</li></ul></li><li style="box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 0.65em; list-style-type: decimal; margin-left: 8px; margin-top: 0.65em;">Copy the trusted CA certificate (PEM file) from the GW or DPS , and import the file as the trusted certificate.<ol style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0.3em 0px 0px 3.2em; padding: 0px; list-style-image: none;"><li style="box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 0.65em; list-style-type: lower-alpha; margin-left: 4px; margin-top: 0.65em;">When adding the node to the gateway system, export the trusted certificate from the gateway as follows:<br style="box-sizing: border-box;"><code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, &quot;Liberation Mono&quot;, &quot;Courier New&quot;, monospace; color: rgb(232, 62, 140); background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); border-width: 1px; border-style: solid; border-color: rgb(234, 236, 240); border-radius: 2px; font-size: 13.125px; word-break: break-word; padding: 2px 5px !important;">ovcert –exporttrusted –file &lt;trusted certificate file&gt;</code></li><li style="box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 0.65em; list-style-type: lower-alpha; margin-left: 4px; margin-top: 0.65em;">Copy&nbsp;<code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, &quot;Liberation Mono&quot;, &quot;Courier New&quot;, monospace; color: rgb(232, 62, 140); background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); border-width: 1px; border-style: solid; border-color: rgb(234, 236, 240); border-radius: 2px; font-size: 13.125px; word-break: break-word; padding: 2px 5px !important;">&lt;trusted certificate file&gt;</code>&nbsp;to the Operations Agent node.</li><li style="box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 0.65em; list-style-type: lower-alpha; margin-left: 4px; margin-top: 0.65em;">On the Operations Agent node, import the trusted certificate:&nbsp;<code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, &quot;Liberation Mono&quot;, &quot;Courier New&quot;, monospace; color: rgb(232, 62, 140); background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); border-width: 1px; border-style: solid; border-color: rgb(234, 236, 240); border-radius: 2px; font-size: 13.125px; word-break: break-word; padding: 2px 5px !important;">ovcert –importtrusted –file &lt;trusted certificate file&gt;</code><br style="box-sizing: border-box;">An example is as shown in the following image:<br style="box-sizing: border-box;"><a href="https://docs.microfocus.com/itomw/File:OBM_2018.05_CAimag14.PNG" class="image" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(58, 131, 230); background: none transparent;"><img alt="OBM 2018.05 CAimag14.PNG" src="https://docs.microfocus.com/mediawiki/images/9/9f/OBM_2018.05_CAimag14.PNG" width="769" height="242" data-file-width="769" data-file-height="242" style="box-sizing: border-box; border: none; vertical-align: middle; max-width: 100%;"></a></li></ol></li><li style="box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 0.65em; list-style-type: decimal; margin-left: 8px; margin-top: 0.65em;">Using the certificate file (root /intermediate CA) and the Operations Agent node core identifier as the CN, generate the CSR. From the CSR, create the certificate P12 file.</li><li style="box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 0.65em; list-style-type: decimal; margin-left: 8px; margin-top: 0.65em;">Import the certificate using the ovcert command:&nbsp;<code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, &quot;Liberation Mono&quot;, &quot;Courier New&quot;, monospace; color: rgb(232, 62, 140); background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); border-width: 1px; border-style: solid; border-color: rgb(234, 236, 240); border-radius: 2px; font-size: 13.125px; word-break: break-word; padding: 2px 5px !important;">ovcert –importcert –file &lt;P12 file&gt;</code><br style="box-sizing: border-box;">After importing the certificate re-start the process using the&nbsp;<code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, &quot;Liberation Mono&quot;, &quot;Courier New&quot;, monospace; color: rgb(232, 62, 140); background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); border-width: 1px; border-style: solid; border-color: rgb(234, 236, 240); border-radius: 2px; font-size: 13.125px; word-break: break-word; padding: 2px 5px !important;">ovc –restart</code>&nbsp;command as shown in the following image:<br style="box-sizing: border-box;"><a href="https://docs.microfocus.com/itomw/File:OBM_2018.05_CAimag15.PNG" class="image" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(58, 131, 230); background: none transparent;"><img alt="OBM 2018.05 CAimag15.PNG" src="https://docs.microfocus.com/mediawiki/images/e/ec/OBM_2018.05_CAimag15.PNG" width="687" height="241" data-file-width="687" data-file-height="241" style="box-sizing: border-box; border: none; vertical-align: middle; max-width: 100%;"></a></li></ol><div name="Validate[edit|editsource]" data-unique="Validate[edit|editsource]" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;; font-size: 15px;"></div><h2 style="box-sizing: border-box; background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; font-weight: 500; margin: 25px 0px 6px; overflow: hidden; padding-top: 0em; padding-bottom: 0.17em; border-bottom: none; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;; line-height: 1.2; letter-spacing: normal; text-transform: none; color: rgb(0, 115, 231) !important; font-size: 24px !important;"><span class="mw-headline" id="Validate" style="box-sizing: border-box;">Validate</span></h2><p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1rem; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;; font-size: 15px; letter-spacing: normal;">To ensure that the certificate installation and creation of secure communication infrastructure is proper end to end, deploy a set of sample monitoring policies from the OBM Server to the Operations Agent, and verify if events are flowing in to the OBM system from the Operations Agent system.</p><div name="Relatedtopics[edit|editsource]" data-unique="Relatedtopics[edit|editsource]" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;; font-size: 15px;"></div><h2 style="box-sizing: border-box; background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; font-weight: 500; margin: 25px 0px 6px; overflow: hidden; padding-top: 0em; padding-bottom: 0.17em; border-bottom: none; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;; line-height: 1.2; letter-spacing: normal; text-transform: none; color: rgb(0, 115, 231) !important; font-size: 24px !important;"><span class="mw-headline" id="Related_topics" style="box-sizing: border-box;">Related topics</span></h2><p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1rem; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;; font-size: 15px; letter-spacing: normal;"><a target="1" rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://docs.microfocus.com/itom/Operations_Agent:12.10/Home" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(58, 131, 230); background: none transparent; font-size: 15px !important;">Operations Agent</a></p>